<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880708-0022 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief: Noted... </HL><SO> </SO><CO> TL MLL WNEWS </CO><TEXT>   WHO'S NEWS: Carolyn Reidy was named president and publisher of Avon Books, a mass-market and trade paperback book publisher owned by Hearst Corp., New York. She succeeds Rena Wolner, who is retiring from publishing.    Time Inc. named Bruce A. Barnet president and chief executive officer of Asiaweek Ltd. and president of Time Inc. Magazines-Asia.    Macmillan Inc., New York, named Harvey Miller vice president of operational finance, a new post at the publisher. He was vice president of asset management. </TEXT></DOC>